This paper deals with the complexity of multiwinner voting rules, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and inapproximability results, which are topics in approximation algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithms presented in the paper are based on optimization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also includes experimental evaluation of the algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and social influence (cs.SI).
